{"lemma":"رُفاتِ","slug":"رُفاتِ","root":"ر.ف.ت","root_slug":"ر-ف-ت","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ف-ت","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رُفات","root":"رفت","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16098"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8F%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16098","headword_ar":"رُفَاتٌ","root":"rft","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A thing, (M,) an old and decayed bone, (A, TA,) or anything, (L, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broken, broken in pieces, crushed, bruised, brayed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pounded;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crumbled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broken into small pieces with the hand;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA;) or a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has become old and worn out, and crumbled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broken into small pieces:"},{"kind":"text","text":"('Ináyeh, TA: [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marofuwtN","text_ar":"مَرْفُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broken,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crumbled, particles; fragments,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crumbs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing that is dry, (T, S, A, K, TA,) of any kind; (T;) [as, for instance,] of musk. (A, TA.) Hence, in the Kur [xvii. 52 and 100],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ay^i*aA kun~aA EiZaAmFA warufaAtFA","text_ar":"اَيِذَا كُنَّا عِظَامًا وَرُفَاتًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When we shall have become bones and broken particles?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, TA.) [Hence also the phrase]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA birofaAtika","text_ar":"لَا بِرْفَاتِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meaning No, by thy ancestors who have become broken and crumbled bones in the dust."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 634.) And [hence one says,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa Al~a*iY A^aEaAda","text_ar":"هُوَ الَّذِى اَعَادَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmakaArima waA^aHoyaA rufaAtahaA waA^ano$ara A^amowaAtahaA","text_ar":"المَكَارِمَ وَاَحْيَا رُفَاتَهَا وَاَنْشَرَ اَمْوَاتَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is the person who has restored generous qualities"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"actions, and revived such of them as had decayed, and brought to life again such of them as had become dead"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","A","TA","L","T","S","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}